        "formula": "The transposed 3D convolution operation with parameters: stride S=1, padding P=0, dilation Dil=1, output_padding OP=0, groups=1, bias=False.\nInput X has shape [N, C_in, D_in, H_in, W_in] = [8, 48, 96, 96, 96].\nWeight W has shape [C_in, C_out, K, K, K] = [48, 24, 3, 3, 3].\nOutput Y has shape [N, C_out, D_out, H_out, W_out] = [8, 24, 98, 98, 98].\nOutput spatial dimensions are given by: D_out = (D_in - 1)*S - 2*P + Dil*(K - 1) + OP + 1 = 98, similarly for H_out and W_out.\nFor each output position (n, o, d, h, w):\n  Y[n,o,d,h,w] = sum_{i=0}^{C_in-1} sum_{kd=0}^{K-1} sum_{kh=0}^{K-1} sum_{kw=0}^{K-1} X[n, i, d_in, h_in, w_in] * W[i, o, kd, kh, kw]\nwhere d_in = (d + P - kd * Dil) / S, h_in = (h + P - kh * Dil) / S, w_in = (w + P - kw * Dil) / S.\nWhen any of d_in, h_in, w_in is not an integer or falls outside [0, D_in-1]×[0, H_in-1]×[0, W_in-1], the corresponding X term is taken as 0 (implicit zero-padding).\nWith the given parameters, the indices simplify to: d_in = d - kd, h_in = h - kh, w_in = w - kw.",
        "boundary_treatment": "Implicit zero-padding: when the computed input indices d_in = d - kd, h_in = h - kh, w_in = w - kw fall outside the valid range [0, D_in-1] × [0, H_in-1] × [0, W_in-1], the corresponding X value is treated as 0. This is equivalent to padding the input X with 2 zeros on each side of every spatial dimension (since (K-1)*Dil - P = 2 with K=3, Dil=1, P=0).",
